ShortName: Clustering (k-means & hierarchical)
Topic: linear-algebra
Concepts: k-means clustering (assign to nearest centroid and update centroids),
 initialization sensitivity (random starts),
 within-cluster sum of squares (WCSS),
 hierarchical agglomerative clustering,
 linkage types (single, complete, average, Ward's),
 dendrograms and cutting them,
 choosing k (elbow method),
 kmeans() hclust() and cutree() in R
BuildsOn: [distance-similarity-and-geometry](distance-similarity-and-geometry/lesson.qmd),
 [mean-variance-covariance](mean-variance-covariance/lesson.qmd)
UsedBy: —
